{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2328333e-8a4c-4f8d-91db-801a9868f1e7","content":"Here's what to change:\n\n1. **Update NuGet packages:**\n   - Upgrade `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **v5.0.0+** (it bundles Microsoft.Testing.Platform support).\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` — it's no longer needed.\n   - Add `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` if you need coverage (optional).\n\n2. **Add an MSBuild property** in your `.csproj` (or `Directory.Build.props`):\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Run tests** the same way:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   With the property above, `dotnet test` routes through Microsoft.Testing.Platform instead of VSTest.\n\n**Key notes:**\n- NUnit3TestAdapter **v5+** acts as the bridge to Microsoft.Testing.Platform — no separate `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` package is needed.\n- `.runsettings` files are still supported but some VSTest-specific options may behave differently.\n- If you use `dotnet test --filter`, the filter syntax remains the same.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"00e83bc1-75b3-4c39-99ec-27e98983c593","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question - I don't need to look at any code. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":365},"id":"8ca41f53-672b-4c6c-8120-c7fc1e1761ea","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:43:09.703Z","parentId":"ceac9d79-2c20-43c4-bb70-2413f146a04e"}
